VBeginning with the Sriraga kritiKarunachoodumu, he followed it withKamakshi Naato(Begada) andNanubrovu Lalitha(Lalitha).Also critically comparing the intricacies involved with those in the compositions of Thyagaraja and Dikshitar in the same ragas, he made it an enlightening exercise.  He rendered the Anandabhairavi kirtanaJagadambaexplaining the specialities of Shyama Sastri&#8217;s adaptation of Vilambagathi and the intertwining of the Sahitya with Chittaswaras on one hand and his uniqueness using Anataragandharam and Kakalinishadam giving an ever extant form of popular appeal to the raga. Continuing with the same fervour after rendering the Duritakaala kirtanaParakela Nanupaalimpa(Kedaragoula), he expatiatedKamakshi(Varali) andSarojadalanetri(Sankarabharanam) explaining how the three facets &#8211;pallavi, anupallaviandcharanams of the kirtanas provide equal scope for executing the neraval felicitously.
